For installing in a hardware machine we would only need an installation 
medium that contain the ISO. The ISO has to be burned with Balena or Ventoy 
>>Ventoy is more efficient, it can handle many OS in only a USB, 
this is a great advantage in terms of resources.

	°Limit the core (CPU's) to max half of the available 

	°Uncheck the Floppy and Network in the boot order and 
	the heirarchy should be first the Hard Disk and after the Optical
	°Check that the EFI is checked in the System Motherboard 
